---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import CTASection from '../../components/CTASection';
import ServiceForm from '../../components/ServiceForm';
import Reviews from '../../components/Reviews';
import LicenseBadges from '../../components/LicenseBadges.astro';
import BrandsSection from '../../components/BrandsSection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Furnace Repair Rancho Santa Margarita | HiLo Heating and Air" description="Fast, reliable furnace repair in Rancho Santa Margarita, CA. Same-day service from licensed technicians at HiLo Heating and Air.">
  <Header />
  <main>
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-blue to-blue-800 py-20 sm:py-28">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Furnace Repair Rancho Santa Margarita</h1>
        <p class="text-white/80 text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">It doesn't get freezing here often. But when a cold snap hits and your furnace decides that's the moment to act up, HiLo Heating and Air takes care of it.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <LicenseBadges />

    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-lg">
        <p>It doesn't get freezing here often. But when a cold snap hits and your furnace decides that's the moment to act up, it's miserable timing. Hilo Heating and Air takes care of <strong>furnace repair Rancho Santa Margarita</strong> homeowners need, whether it's a quick fix or something that's been building for a while.</p>

        <h2>The Warning Signs Worth Paying Attention To</h2>
        <p>Furnaces don't usually quit without warning. There's a noise that wasn't there before. A room that stays cold no matter what the thermostat says. A pilot light that keeps going out. Sometimes there's a smell — faintly burnt, or something a little off when the system kicks on, and that one's worth checking right away, not waiting on. People tend to call us for <strong>furnace repair Rancho Santa Margarita</strong> after noticing one of these for a week or two, hoping it'll resolve on its own. It usually doesn't.</p>

        <h2>What's Actually Going Wrong, Most of the Time</h2>
        <p>A dead ignitor shows up a lot. So does a blower motor on its way out, or a flame sensor coated in just enough grime to trip the safety shutoff. Thermostats miscommunicate sometimes too — looks like a furnace problem, isn't really one. Then there's the rarer, more serious stuff: a cracked heat exchanger, which isn't something to put off fixing. Either way, before any part gets swapped, <strong>furnace repair Rancho Santa Margarita</strong> jobs start with an actual diagnosis — not a guess dressed up as one.</p>

        <h2>Getting to You Quickly</h2>
        <p>Cold houses don't wait well, and neither should you have to. Most repairs get same-day or next-morning appointments, trucks carry the parts that fail most often, and the majority of jobs finish in a single visit. That's the goal behind <strong>furnace repair Rancho Santa Margarita</strong> service — get there fast, fix it right, don't make you call twice.</p>

        <h2>Local, and It Shows</h2>
        <p>We're not driving in from somewhere far. Being based nearby means knowing the housing styles, the typical furnace setups, what tends to fail first given the climate here. Every job's done to code, backed by a guarantee — if something feels off after we leave, we're close enough to come back and sort it.</p>
        <p>If your furnace's acting up, give Hilo Heating and Air a call. Better to fix it properly now than deal with the same problem again in a month.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
          <div>
            <span class="inline-block bg-brand-blue/10 text-brand-blue text-sm font-semibold px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full mb-4">Schedule Service</span>
            <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-brand-blue mb-4">Get a Free Estimate</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">Fill out the form and our team will get back to you within 15 minutes. Same-day service available.</p>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-blue/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-blue" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 6v6h4.5m4.5 0a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-blue">Same-Day Service Available</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-blue/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-blue" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12.75L11.25 15 15 9.75m-3-7.036A11.959 11.959 0 013.598 6 11.99 11.99 0 003 9.749c0 5.592 3.824 10.29 9 11.623 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.31-.21-2.571-.598-3.751h-.152c-3.196 0-6.1-1.248-8.25-3.285z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-blue">Free Diagnostics with Repair</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand-blue/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-blue" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M2.25 18.75a60.07 60.07 0 0115.797 2.101c.727.198 1.453-.342 1.453-1.096V18.75M3.75 4.5v.75A.75.75 0 013 6h-.75m0 0v-.375c0-.621.504-1.125 1.125-1.125H20.25M2.25 6v9m18-10.5v.75c0 .414.336.75.75.75h.75m-1.5-1.5h.375c.621 0 1.125.504 1.125 1.125v9.75c0 .621-.504 1.125-1.125 1.125h-.375m1.5-1.5H21a.75.75 0 00-.75.75v.75m0 0H3.75m0 0h-.375a1.125 1.125 0 01-1.125-1.125V15m1.5 1.5v-.75A.75.75 0 003 15h-.75M15 10.5a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm3 0h.008v.008H18V10.5zm-12 0h.008v.008H6V10.5z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-blue">Upfront Pricing, No Hidden Fees</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <ServiceForm client:load />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <Reviews client:visible />
    <BrandsSection />

    <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 bg-slate-50">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-blue mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">There's a faint burnt smell when my furnace starts. Worth worrying about?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Yes — could be harmless dust burning off, could be something more serious. Worth having it checked rather than guessing.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">How fast can you get out here?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Same-day, most of the time. Next morning if things are busy.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">Repair or replace — how do I know which makes sense?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Depends on the age and what's actually wrong. We'll tell you straight, not just push a sale.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">Do you give a price before starting?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Always — nothing gets done until you know the cost.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">How often should the furnace get checked?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Once a year, ideally before it gets cold, so problems get caught before they become no-heat emergencies.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">What brands do you service?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Most major ones — wide range of systems and ages.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">Are the technicians licensed?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Yes, every one, fully licensed and insured.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-brand-blue/10">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-brand-blue mb-2">What happens if the issue comes back?</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">Covered under our guarantee — just call and we'll handle it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-brand-blue/5 py-8">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
        <p class="text-brand-blue font-semibold">Hilo Heating and Air · 8131 Electric Ave, Stanton, CA 90680, United States</p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 mt-1"><a href="tel:+17148535534" class="hover:text-brand-red transition">(714) 853-5534</a> · <a href="mailto:info@hiloheatingandair.com" class="hover:text-brand-red transition">info@hiloheatingandair.com</a></p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <CTASection client:visible />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
